{"label":"Command Line Interface (CLI)","id":"cli","list":[{"label":"Multiple Choice Question","type":"mcq","id":"test","commonData":{"title":"Multiple Choice Question","allowFrac":false},"data":[{"questions":[{"qText":"Which command is used to list files and directories in Linux?","options":"ls\nlist\nshow\ndirlist"},{"qText":"Which command is used to change the current directory?","options":"cd\nchdir\nchangedir\npath"},{"qText":"Which command is used to display the current working directory?","options":"pwd\ncwd\nwhere\npath"},{"qText":"Which command is used to create a new directory in Linux?","options":"mkdir\nnewdir\nmakedir\ndircreate"},{"qText":"Which command is used to remove a directory in Linux?","options":"rmdir\nremovedir\ndeldir\ndirrm"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Which command is used to copy files in Linux?","options":"cp\ncopy\ncfile\ncpx"},{"qText":"Which command is used to move or rename files in Linux?","options":"mv\nmove\nren\ntrans"},{"qText":"Which command is used to remove files in Linux?","options":"rm\ndelete\nerase\ndelfile"},{"qText":"Which command is used to display the contents of a text file in Linux?","options":"cat\nshow\nprint\nopen"},{"qText":"Which command is used to clear the terminal screen in Linux?","options":"clear\nclr\ncls\nclean"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Which command is used to search for text in files in Linux?","options":"grep\nfindtext\nsearch\nlookfor"},{"qText":"Which command is used to display running processes in Linux?","options":"ps\nproc\nprocesslist\ntask"},{"qText":"Which command is used to display disk usage in Linux?","options":"df\ndu\ndiskinfo\nstorage"},{"qText":"Which command is used to display the manual pages of other commands in Linux?","options":"man\nhelp\ninfo\ncmdman"},{"qText":"Which command is used to exit the CLI terminal in Linux?","options":"exit\nquit\nclose\nend"}]}]},{"id":"match","label":"Match the Following","type":"match","onlyBigScreen":true,"data":{"title":"Match the Following","fontSize":"1.5rem","canvasWidth":1000,"leftSideWidth":400,"rightSizeWidth":500,"allowFrac":false,"text":"Creates a new directory named project | mkdir project\nDeletes a file named file.txt | rm file.txt\nDisplays the current working directory | pwd\nLists files and folders in the current directory | ls\nRenames or moves a file | mv old.txt new.txt\nCopies contents of file1.txt into file2.txt | cp file1.txt file2.txt\nMoves one directory level up | cd ..\nClears the terminal screen | clear"}},{"type":"classifySentence","label":"True or False","id":"true-false","data":{"title":"True or False","types":[{"name":"True","text":"The command 'ls' is used to list files and directories.\nThe command 'cd' is used to change the current working directory.\nThe command 'pwd' prints the current working directory.\nThe command 'mkdir' is used to create a new directory.\nThe command 'rm' is used to delete files."},{"name":"False","text":"The command 'man' is used to move or rename files.\nThe command 'exit' is used to list all files in a directory.\nThe command 'cat' is used to shut down the system.\nThe command 'grep' is used to clear the terminal screen.\nThe command 'ps' is used to print the contents of a file."}]}},{"id":"fillup","label":"Fill in the blanks","type":"fillup","data":{"title":"Fill in the blanks","fontSize":"1.4rem","text":"The command used to list files and directories in Linux is *ls (list, dirlist)*.\nThe command used to change the current directory is *cd (chdir, path)*.\nThe command used to print the current working directory is *pwd (cwd, where)*.\nThe command used to create a new directory is *mkdir (newdir, makedir)*.\nThe command used to remove an empty directory is *rmdir (removedir, deldir)*.\nThe command used to copy files is *cp (copy, cpx)*.\nThe command used to move or rename files is *mv (move, ren)*.\nThe command used to remove files is *rm (delete, erase)*.\nThe command used to display the contents of a text file is *cat (show, print)*.\nThe command used to clear the terminal screen is *clear (cls, clean) * ."}}]}